PHASE 2 — NON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS (SECURITY & QUALITY)

NFR-SEC-001: Authentication & Session Management
- NFR-SEC-001.1: The system shall support authentication using OAuth2/OIDC providers.
- NFR-SEC-001.2: The system shall support multiple external identity providers.
- NFR-SEC-001.3: Access tokens shall have a limited lifetime.
- NFR-SEC-001.4: Refresh tokens shall have a longer but finite lifetime.
- NFR-SEC-001.5: User sessions shall expire after a period of inactivity.
- NFR-SEC-001.6: Authentication behavior shall be configurable without code changes.

NFR-SEC-002: Multi-Tenancy Isolation
- NFR-SEC-002.1: The system shall enforce strict logical isolation between tenants.
- NFR-SEC-002.2: A request shall only access data belonging to its active tenant.
- NFR-SEC-002.3: Tenant context shall be validated on every request.
- NFR-SEC-002.4: Cross-tenant data access shall be treated as a critical failure.
- NFR-SEC-002.5: Tenant isolation shall be verifiable through testing and review.

NFR-SEC-003: Data Protection
- NFR-SEC-003.1: All external and internal communications shall be encrypted in transit.
- NFR-SEC-003.2: Sensitive data at rest shall be protected using industry-standard encryption.
- NFR-SEC-003.3: Secrets and credentials shall not be stored in plaintext.
- NFR-SEC-003.4: Authentication credentials and API secrets shall be stored securely.
- NFR-SEC-003.5: Cryptographic controls shall be centrally managed and rotatable.

NFR-SEC-004: Auditability & Logging
- NFR-SEC-004.1: Security-relevant events shall be logged.
- NFR-SEC-004.2: Authentication and authorization events shall be auditable.
- NFR-SEC-004.3: Administrative actions shall be logged with sufficient context.
- NFR-SEC-004.4: Logs shall be protected from unauthorized modification.
- NFR-SEC-004.5: Logs shall be retained for a defined retention period.
- NFR-SEC-004.6: Audit data shall support incident investigation and forensics.

NFR-SEC-005: Operational Security
- NFR-SEC-005.1: Security controls shall not significantly degrade system performance.
- NFR-SEC-005.2: Security-critical configuration shall be externally configurable.
- NFR-SEC-005.3: The system shall support periodic security testing and reviews.
- NFR-SEC-005.4: Security failures shall be observable and alertable.
